            ">
        Netflix and stress
        </h2>  
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        Netflix runs so smoothly that it’s easy to forget what it takes to keep it that way. The secret weapon behind the sorcery is the open-source tool called <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-07-06-2025-chaos-monkey" target="_blank">Chaos Monkey</a>. It operates based on chaos engineering, where engineers intentionally induce controlled failures in the system to assess its resilience and implement improvements. By simulating server crashes, bugs, or network hiccups, Netflix tests its platform’s ability to respond and mitigate crises.
          </p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/chaos-monkey-random-failure-testing-netflix.jpg" alt="Chaos Monkey operates by randomly selecting virtual machine instances and shutting them down during business hours" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>
            Chaos Monkey operates by randomly selecting virtual machine instances and shutting them down during business hours. Credits: Netflix</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Chaos Monkey starts by picking a potential system failure, database failure, and artificially inserts that failure in a carefully controlled way. As the chaos unfolds in a controlled environment, engineers keep a close eye on how the system performs. This data helps pinpoint weaknesses and areas for improvement.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The goal is to ensure the platform remains operational even in the event of an issue, with backups in place. It also tests recovery speed and builds confidence in the system. Similar to the chaos monkey, Amazon has a fault simulator, Spotify stress-tests its microservices, and Uber intentionally causes backend confusion.
            </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column> 
    </mj-section>


